result.execSummary:
The defendant Patrice L Turner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant  examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty of Counts 1 and 2 as charged in the Amended Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  Parties request another date for sentencing.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 20.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 9, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Patrice L Turner in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Amended Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty.

/submitted by the State, received and filed.  Defendant is now charged as follows:
COUNT 01:  Misdemeanor Theft - Intentionally Take, a Class A Misdemeanor, contrary to Wis. Stats. section 943.50(1m)(b) and (4)(a).
COUNT 02:  Fleeing, a Misdemeanor, contrary to Wis. Stats. sections 346.04(2t), 346.17(2t).
